title: Udaan
overview: Expelled from his school, a 16-year old boy returns home to his abusive and oppressive father.

title: Vivre sa vie: Film en douze tableaux
overview: Twelve episodic tales in the life of a Parisian woman and her slow descent into prostitution.

title: Philadelphia
overview: When a man with HIV is fired by his law firm because of his condition, he hires a homophobic small time lawyer as the only willing advocate for a wrongful dismissal suit.

title: Boyhood
overview: The life of Mason, from early childhood to his arrival at college.

title: Lifeboat
overview: Several survivors of a torpedoed merchant ship in World War II find themselves in the same lifeboat with one of the crew members of the U-boat that sank their ship.

title: Wonder
overview: Based on the New York Times bestseller, this movie tells the incredibly inspiring and heartwarming story of August Pullman, a boy with facial differences who enters the fifth grade, attending a mainstream elementary school for the first time.

title: Platoon
overview: Chris Taylor, a neophyte recruit in Vietnam, finds himself caught in a battle of wills between two sergeants, one good and the other evil. A shrewd examination of the brutality of war and the duality of man in conflict.

title: Network
overview: A television network cynically exploits a deranged former anchor's ravings and revelations about the news media for its own profit.

title: Creed
overview: The former World Heavyweight Champion Rocky Balboa serves as a trainer and mentor to Adonis Johnson, the son of his late friend and former rival Apollo Creed.

title: Magnolia
overview: An epic mosaic of interrelated characters in search of love, forgiveness, and meaning in the San Fernando Valley.

title: Babam ve Oglum
overview: The family of a left-wing journalist is torn apart after the military coup of Turkey in 1980.

title: Viskningar och rop
overview: When a woman dying of cancer in early twentieth-century Sweden is visited by her two sisters, long-repressed feelings between the siblings rise to the surface.

title: Capharnaüm
overview: While serving a five-year sentence for a violent crime, a 12-year-old boy sues his parents for neglect.
stars: ['Zain Al Rafeea', 'Yordanos Shiferaw', 'Boluwatife Treasure Bankole', 'Kawsar Al Haddad']

title: Darbareye Elly
overview: The mysterious disappearance of a kindergarten teacher during a picnic in the north of Iran is followed by a series of misadventures for her fellow travelers.

title: Gegen die Wand
overview: With the intention to break free from the strict familial restrictions, a suicidal young woman sets up a marriage of convenience with a forty-year-old addict, an act that will lead to an outburst of envious love.

title: Auf der anderen Seite
overview: A Turkish man travels to Istanbul to find the daughter of his father's former girlfriend.

title: Jodaeiye Nader az Simin
overview: A married couple are faced with a difficult decision - to improve the life of their child by moving to another country or to stay in Iran and look after a deteriorating parent who has Alzheimer's disease.

title: La grande bellezza
overview: Jep Gambardella has seduced his way through the lavish nightlife of Rome for decades, but after his 65th birthday and a shock from the past, Jep looks past the nightclubs and parties to find a timeless landscape of absurd, exquisite beauty.

title: Die Welle
overview: A high school teacher's experiment to demonstrate to his students what life is like under a dictatorship spins horribly out of control when he forms a social unit with a life of its own.

title: Kokuhaku
overview: A psychological thriller of a grieving mother turned cold-blooded avenger with a twisty master plan to pay back those who were responsible for her daughter's death.
